00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:25,890 --> 00:00:28,650
"Sophie's life was what you'd call perfect."

2
00:00:36,850 --> 00:00:40,610
[Average grade point: 3.96]

3
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:52,050
Why didn't you get a 4.0?

4
00:01:08,050 --> 00:01:09,970
"Raised to be..."

5
00:01:13,570 --> 00:01:14,730
"...proper."

6
00:01:17,890 --> 00:01:19,250
Mom, what's wrong?!

7
00:01:28,890 --> 00:01:30,610
"It had to be absolutely perfect."

8
00:02:06,450 --> 00:02:07,730
Sophie, what are you watching?

9
00:02:16,450 --> 00:02:18,290
Why are you watching this kind of stuff?

10
00:02:20,690 --> 00:02:22,570
Did I raise you poorly?

11
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:27,650
It's my fault. It's all my fault.

12
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:32,730
That's why you turned out like this!

13
00:02:32,730 --> 00:02:34,210
"Sophie learned right then..."

14
00:02:34,850 --> 00:02:36,970
I won't do it again, Mom.

15
00:02:44,090 --> 00:02:46,010
I'll never do it again.

16
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:48,330
"...that she couldn't afford to make any mistakes."

17
00:02:48,330 --> 00:02:50,450
I love you most, Mom.

18
00:02:51,410 --> 00:02:53,650
Just stay within the lines I've drawn for you.

19
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:56,930
And everything will be fine, sweetie.

20
00:04:02,330 --> 00:04:04,970
"Amy's life was never perfect."

21
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:08,770
Ugh, my daughter doesn't care about a single thing.

22
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:11,250
Yeah, I'm talking about Amy.

23
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:13,530
The youngest one who isn't good at school.

24
00:04:15,890 --> 00:04:18,970
And lately, she's so addicted to social media.

25
00:04:19,210 --> 00:04:21,410
She's always on her phone.

26
00:04:21,410 --> 00:04:23,010
I don't know what she does all day.

27
00:04:23,010 --> 00:04:25,130
I don't even know if she'll get accepted anywhere.

28
00:04:26,810 --> 00:04:30,570
But thank goodness my son got into med school.

29
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,810
So that's one less headache.

30
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:37,730
But my daughter really stresses me out.

31
00:05:01,730 --> 00:05:04,090
"As long as we're in the right place,"

32
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:24,370
"we'll be the right person."

33
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:18,410
Hi, P'Amy.

34
00:06:18,410 --> 00:06:20,290
Hi.

35
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:28,690
See you later.

36
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:59,050
What?

37
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:02,770
Nothing.

38
00:08:35,010 --> 00:08:36,170
Oh.

39
00:08:36,690 --> 00:08:38,090
Should I wait for you?

40
00:08:40,010 --> 00:08:41,290
It's fine.

41
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:50,770
Sorry I'm late. I was at practice.

42
00:09:14,570 --> 00:09:16,770
Do you have a pencil I could borrow?

43
00:09:17,210 --> 00:09:18,770
I forgot mine.

44
00:09:26,530 --> 00:09:27,730
Thanks.

45
00:09:49,810 --> 00:09:51,410
I didn't study.

46
00:09:51,850 --> 00:09:54,610
I figured guessing the same letter gives me a better chance.

47
00:09:58,290 --> 00:10:03,130
Hey, sorry for startling you that day.

48
00:10:03,890 --> 00:10:05,050
What day?

49
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:09,330
The day you saw me kissing...

50
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:16,650
Oh.

51
00:10:17,330 --> 00:10:18,730
I wasn't startled.

52
00:10:19,170 --> 00:10:22,410
Really? I thought you would be.

53
00:10:22,970 --> 00:10:25,890
Since you seem like such a proper girl.

54
00:10:27,810 --> 00:10:29,290
Do I look proper?

55
00:10:29,810 --> 00:10:32,810
I mean, you're the student council president.

56
00:10:32,810 --> 00:10:35,770
Seeing something like that must have felt weird, right?

57
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:39,970
But thanks for not telling the teachers.

58
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:44,210
I'm not a snitch.

59
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:47,650
And I'm not a proper girl either.

60
00:10:53,130 --> 00:10:54,290
True.

61
00:10:54,770 --> 00:10:56,490
A pretty girl like you...

62
00:10:57,610 --> 00:10:59,850
must have some experience by now, right?

63
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:04,090
What do you mean?

64
00:11:04,090 --> 00:11:06,050
I mean,

65
00:11:06,050 --> 00:11:09,770
you must have people hitting on you, or had a partner before.

66
00:11:10,010 --> 00:11:11,090
And...

67
00:11:11,890 --> 00:11:14,570
you probably have some physical experience, stuff like that.

68
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:18,130
Huh. I don't.

69
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:20,090
Seriously?

70
00:11:20,290 --> 00:11:23,330
So what's the most physical contact you've ever had?

71
00:11:25,410 --> 00:11:26,650
None at all.

72
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:29,170
I haven't even been kissed.

73
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:31,850
Really?

74
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:35,570
So that means you've never slept with anyone?

75
00:11:38,170 --> 00:11:40,450
More like I haven't found anyone I want to try it with.

76
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:49,130
But honestly, I am curious.

77
00:11:49,490 --> 00:11:50,930
About how it feels.

78
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:55,730
What do you mean?

79
00:11:58,410 --> 00:12:01,250
When people actually have sex.

80
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:03,490
With this kind of thing,

81
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:07,930
you have to try it yourself to understand.

82
00:12:15,050 --> 00:12:16,770
Just like this exam.

83
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,050
If you don't actually do the work,

84
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:22,170
you'll never understand it.

85
00:12:51,370 --> 00:12:54,730
There, I helped you with your exam.

86
00:12:57,490 --> 00:12:59,690
Now, I want to know how it feels.

87
00:13:00,810 --> 00:13:02,450
You have to return the favor.

88
00:13:11,450 --> 00:13:14,370
"And maybe the right place..."

89
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:19,850
"...is what leads us to the right person."

90
00:13:25,490 --> 00:13:28,410
"The perfection that Amy never knew..."

91
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:33,930
"Finally,"

92
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,970
"Amy made it hers."

93
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:30,530
Wow, back with another love song today.

94
00:14:30,570 --> 00:14:33,530
When are you going to reveal who's in your heart, P'Amy?

95
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:41,050
Honestly, you could reveal it today.

96
00:14:41,810 --> 00:14:43,610
Go ahead, tell us.

97
00:14:43,610 --> 00:14:45,570
The 'S' stands for...

98
00:14:45,890 --> 00:14:48,530
The 'S' stands for...

99
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:01,890
Sabrina Carpenter.

100
00:15:03,450 --> 00:15:05,570
Oh, come on, P'Amy!

101
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:09,290
I mean, it's still unrequited love right now.

102
00:15:16,450 --> 00:15:19,650
Our students' standards are steadily dropping.

103
00:15:20,370 --> 00:15:22,130
Just look at the radio show.

104
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:25,210
When Teacher Nalin was a student, it was all about general knowledge.

105
00:15:25,210 --> 00:15:26,730
Look at it now.

106
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:29,930
Financial problems, romance issues.

107
00:15:29,930 --> 00:15:34,050
And some are secretly doing inappropriate things behind our backs.

108
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:39,010
Nalin, do you happen to know anything about these issues?

109
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:44,210
I don't really like gossiping about students.

110
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:53,010
Teacher,

111
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,610
The Class C students are fighting!

112
00:16:01,690 --> 00:16:03,890
Are you crazy, Belle!

113
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,850
Stop!

114
00:16:05,890 --> 00:16:07,290
Belle!

115
00:16:10,610 --> 00:16:12,450
Everyone, stop!

116
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,890
Hey, can I have some? I forgot to buy mine.

117
00:17:27,770 --> 00:17:29,330
So forgetful.

118
00:17:32,170 --> 00:17:33,290
Thanks.

119
00:17:34,210 --> 00:17:37,170
If you keep forgetting, I'll buy you some every day.

120
00:17:37,410 --> 00:17:39,010
What about us?

121
00:17:39,730 --> 00:17:41,810
I can buy some for you guys too.

122
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:44,930
Stop teasing her.

123
00:17:44,930 --> 00:17:46,770
Come on, guys, let's go.

124
00:17:54,290 --> 00:17:55,650
Um, P'Amy,

125
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:58,370
I'm coming in for stand cheer practice on Saturday too.

126
00:17:58,370 --> 00:17:59,890
Will you be here?

127
00:18:01,090 --> 00:18:03,250
Oh, I won't be here tomorrow.

128
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:06,010
Going out of town for two days.

129
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:08,370
Oh, really?

130
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:11,090
Going with your family?

131
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:13,970
Oh, going with a friend's family.

132
00:18:15,610 --> 00:18:17,690
I'm going to get back to practice.

133
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:18,810
See ya.

134
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:07,948
You've all explained how this happened.

135
00:19:08,988 --> 00:19:11,668
I think we should discuss the main issue.

136
00:19:11,908 --> 00:19:16,548
Even though this started because of Jiratchaya borrowing money,

137
00:19:17,028 --> 00:19:19,788
the fact that you got physical

138
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:22,908
means you still have to be punished.

139
00:19:23,748 --> 00:19:26,868
A 10-point deduction in behavior.

140
00:19:26,868 --> 00:19:29,628
And 20 hours of community service.

141
00:19:29,628 --> 00:19:32,588
And if there's any more insulting of your peers,

142
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:36,428
you know the punishment won't stop here, right?

143
00:19:38,628 --> 00:19:42,588
Violence is strictly unacceptable here.

144
00:19:43,028 --> 00:19:44,588
Violence

145
00:19:44,908 --> 00:19:47,188
is never the right solution.

146
00:19:47,388 --> 00:19:50,668
A 10-point deduction

147
00:19:51,228 --> 00:19:52,428
isn't enough.

148
00:19:53,388 --> 00:19:56,828
As agreed, if Nicharee causes any more trouble,

149
00:19:57,228 --> 00:20:01,108
she will lose her right to compete in the French competition.

150
00:20:02,508 --> 00:20:04,508
Is that correct, Mother Superior?

151
00:20:09,268 --> 00:20:12,068
Belle! Wait, Belle!

152
00:20:17,068 --> 00:20:19,828
You know you were wrong too, right?

153
00:20:19,828 --> 00:20:22,028
For saying something that harsh.

154
00:20:31,188 --> 00:20:32,588
Student.

155
00:20:32,588 --> 00:20:35,308
Does Nano really have a problem with overspending?

156
00:20:54,508 --> 00:20:55,908
Belle...

157
00:20:58,348 --> 00:21:02,228
Are you okay with not being able to compete together?

158
00:21:09,028 --> 00:21:10,548
I'm not okay with it.

159
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:12,468
But what can I do?

160
00:21:19,068 --> 00:21:21,068
But I still want to help you win.

161
00:21:22,108 --> 00:21:23,428
Wanna study tomorrow?

162
00:21:24,788 --> 00:21:26,908
Yeah, sure.

163
00:21:32,388 --> 00:21:34,148
Hey, Belle...

164
00:21:36,308 --> 00:21:38,108
But tomorrow...

165
00:21:38,108 --> 00:21:39,748
can you help me with that other thing too?

166
00:21:49,348 --> 00:21:52,188
There's a huge rumor going around among the students right now.

167
00:21:53,148 --> 00:21:56,988
About inappropriate relationships within our A.T. school.

168
00:21:58,228 --> 00:22:00,668
Doesn't Teacher Nalin have anything to report on this?

169
00:22:02,228 --> 00:22:03,868
Actually,

170
00:22:04,188 --> 00:22:06,228
I was just about to report it.

171
00:22:08,748 --> 00:22:10,308
It's regarding a romantic relationship.

172
00:22:30,028 --> 00:22:34,108
P'Jane, can I talk to you for a second?

173
00:22:34,308 --> 00:22:35,628
Sure.

174
00:22:37,668 --> 00:22:38,988
Well...

175
00:22:39,548 --> 00:22:43,028
I feel bad for causing a problem between you and P'Nano.

176
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:46,108
About the cheerleading budget P'Nano asked for...

177
00:22:46,708 --> 00:22:49,828
She actually let me borrow it to rent a costume first.

178
00:22:49,828 --> 00:22:51,428
Because I really don't have the money.

179
00:22:52,308 --> 00:22:54,068
I'm so sorry.

180
00:22:55,788 --> 00:22:57,108
Oh.

181
00:23:15,148 --> 00:23:17,068
Did you really con me out of my money?

182
00:23:17,068 --> 00:23:18,988
I gave you that to help the cat.

183
00:23:18,988 --> 00:23:21,108
So you didn't use it to help the cat?

184
00:23:22,868 --> 00:23:24,588
I really did use it for the treatment.

185
00:23:25,428 --> 00:23:26,988
Well, I haven't seen any proof.

186
00:23:26,988 --> 00:23:30,988
I heard your friend say you spent the money on other things.

187
00:23:30,988 --> 00:23:33,388
I can swear to it anywhere you want, Sister.

188
00:23:33,388 --> 00:23:35,308
It's not that I don't believe you.

189
00:23:35,828 --> 00:23:37,628
But it is very suspicious.

190
00:23:38,148 --> 00:23:40,388
But I can actually be a witness to that.

191
00:23:47,788 --> 00:23:50,388
This is the X-ray of the broken bone.

192
00:23:50,388 --> 00:23:53,508
I actually have photos of the treatment process too.

193
00:23:53,508 --> 00:23:55,748
But they're not very pleasant to look at.

194
00:23:56,228 --> 00:23:59,468
Nano, I'm sorry for misunderstanding.

195
00:23:59,468 --> 00:24:01,188
It's completely fine.

196
00:24:02,468 --> 00:24:05,628
Actually, Nano started a fundraising page to help cats.

197
00:24:05,628 --> 00:24:08,788
At first, donors were very skeptical.

198
00:24:08,788 --> 00:24:12,068
But Nano actually does it, and has proof of every step.

199
00:24:12,068 --> 00:24:13,348
As for the leftover money,

200
00:24:13,348 --> 00:24:16,748
Nano donates it to help other stray cats at the end of every month.

201
00:24:18,028 --> 00:24:20,148
Are you really that good of a person?

202
00:24:23,348 --> 00:24:25,828
But what I'm wondering is,

203
00:24:25,828 --> 00:24:28,148
there's still a balance due on this case.

204
00:24:28,148 --> 00:24:30,748
But I haven't seen Nano start a fundraiser for it.

205
00:24:35,148 --> 00:24:38,428
Well, I actually want to keep this cat myself.

206
00:24:38,428 --> 00:24:40,548
So I didn't open a fundraiser for it.

207
00:24:47,028 --> 00:24:48,868
For the remaining treatment cost.

208
00:24:52,668 --> 00:24:54,428
It's okay, Sister.

209
00:24:54,428 --> 00:24:57,108
Consider it an apology from me.

210
00:25:04,788 --> 00:25:06,308
Thank you, Sister.

211
00:25:06,308 --> 00:25:07,548
You're welcome.

212
00:25:21,748 --> 00:25:23,428
Are you going to stare all day?

213
00:25:24,668 --> 00:25:26,588
Are you an angel or something?

214
00:25:26,588 --> 00:25:28,868
Beautiful and charitable.

215
00:25:30,668 --> 00:25:34,188
You sound so old. Major Gen Y vibes.

216
00:25:36,028 --> 00:25:37,628
But I don't get it.

217
00:25:39,148 --> 00:25:41,468
Why do you donate the money?

218
00:25:41,988 --> 00:25:44,028
Couldn't you keep it to help other cats?

219
00:25:46,588 --> 00:25:47,628
No way.

220
00:25:47,828 --> 00:25:50,948
I'm a terrible spender.

221
00:25:50,948 --> 00:25:54,748
If I gave in to temptation and spent the money,

222
00:25:55,588 --> 00:25:57,508
I wouldn't be able to live with myself.

223
00:26:00,748 --> 00:26:02,748
So why did you suddenly decide to keep this one?

224
00:26:11,748 --> 00:26:13,548
I guess we just clicked.

225
00:27:00,748 --> 00:27:02,628
Hey, Nano, wait up!

226
00:27:18,908 --> 00:27:20,628
How do you know where I live?

227
00:27:22,668 --> 00:27:25,188
I know the Mother Superior's computer password.

228
00:27:25,788 --> 00:27:27,468
So...

229
00:27:28,428 --> 00:27:30,708
I got into the school's database a bit.

230
00:28:03,388 --> 00:28:04,588
Teacher.

231
00:28:05,588 --> 00:28:07,028
I'm sorry.

232
00:28:10,828 --> 00:28:13,188
I didn't want to cause so much trouble that I couldn't compete.

233
00:28:13,868 --> 00:28:15,588
I know I let you down.

234
00:28:19,788 --> 00:28:22,068
But I'll help Earn win no matter what.

235
00:28:25,308 --> 00:28:27,068
Do you know where you messed up?

236
00:28:28,748 --> 00:28:31,788
Messed up by not scattering before the teachers came?

237
00:28:33,868 --> 00:28:35,948
You messed up by reacting like that.

238
00:28:35,948 --> 00:28:38,188
I understand

239
00:28:38,188 --> 00:28:41,108
that you were upset and wanted to retaliate.

240
00:28:41,668 --> 00:28:43,748
But there are so many other ways to retaliate

241
00:28:43,748 --> 00:28:45,668
without getting yourself in trouble.

242
00:28:46,428 --> 00:28:48,908
This time, you chose the wrong way.

243
00:28:51,708 --> 00:28:54,228
If something like this happens again,

244
00:28:54,788 --> 00:28:58,548
I hope you don't make the same mistake.

245
00:28:58,548 --> 00:28:59,908
Okay?

246
00:29:01,348 --> 00:29:02,628
Okay.

247
00:29:04,508 --> 00:29:05,988
And...

248
00:29:06,508 --> 00:29:08,388
Does this mean you forgive me?

249
00:29:12,628 --> 00:29:15,988
Phew. It was worth the cab fare then.

250
00:29:15,988 --> 00:29:18,868
I'll call you a ride back. You can go now.

251
00:29:18,868 --> 00:29:20,948
And give me my towel back. My hair is still wet.

252
00:29:27,108 --> 00:29:28,268
Hey!

253
00:29:29,388 --> 00:29:31,348
I'm leaving! Bye!

254
00:29:57,828 --> 00:29:59,348
Hello, Ma'am.

255
00:29:59,348 --> 00:30:01,948
Hello. Come on in.

256
00:30:03,628 --> 00:30:04,908
It's fine.

257
00:30:04,908 --> 00:30:06,828
It's fine. Allow me.

258
00:30:08,428 --> 00:30:09,668
Thank you.

259
00:30:20,548 --> 00:30:22,068
All set.

260
00:30:30,068 --> 00:30:34,028
When did you two become friends? How did you meet?

261
00:30:35,108 --> 00:30:37,548
I met her when I went to take a make-up exam, Ma'am.

262
00:30:40,348 --> 00:30:42,708
Amy is very involved in extracurriculars, Mom.

263
00:30:42,708 --> 00:30:44,628
So she had to take the exam later than the others.

264
00:30:44,628 --> 00:30:48,108
I was proctoring for Teacher Thip at the time, so we met.

265
00:30:50,268 --> 00:30:51,748
Very involved in extracurriculars.

266
00:30:52,068 --> 00:30:53,588
What kind of activities do you do?

267
00:30:53,668 --> 00:30:54,708
- She's a musician.
- I'm an athlete.

268
00:30:55,948 --> 00:30:57,228
- an athlete.
- a musician.

269
00:30:58,988 --> 00:31:01,748
Actually, Amy does almost everything, Mom.

270
00:31:01,748 --> 00:31:04,108
The day you came to shoot the VTR at the school...

271
00:31:04,388 --> 00:31:06,308
that's why she was chosen as a student representative.

272
00:31:09,428 --> 00:31:12,188
Well, since you're so good at activities,

273
00:31:12,188 --> 00:31:14,708
Sophie, you should invite her to play a round with me sometime.

274
00:31:15,108 --> 00:31:16,788
Are you interested in golf?

275
00:31:17,148 --> 00:31:18,788
I can give it a try, Ma'am.

276
00:31:19,788 --> 00:31:20,988
Not afraid of the sun?

277
00:31:21,988 --> 00:31:24,268
I'll just put on some sunscreen.

278
00:31:33,228 --> 00:31:35,268
Let's paint a little more over here.

279
00:31:40,028 --> 00:31:41,708
Is anyone else coming to help?

280
00:31:42,628 --> 00:31:45,228
Yeah, the others will be here soon.

281
00:31:45,748 --> 00:31:46,788
Don't worry about it.

282
00:31:46,788 --> 00:31:49,588
You go focus on studying for your French competition.

283
00:31:49,788 --> 00:31:51,188
Just bring home the win for us.

284
00:31:57,108 --> 00:31:59,668
I got banned from competing.

285
00:32:04,548 --> 00:32:08,508
So... because of Nano, you slapped Khaopan?

286
00:32:10,668 --> 00:32:12,268
How did you come to that conclusion?

287
00:32:15,668 --> 00:32:17,148
I mean, pretty much.

288
00:32:19,468 --> 00:32:21,348
And I was hot-headed too.

289
00:32:21,988 --> 00:32:24,828
But she was asking for it.

290
00:32:25,988 --> 00:32:27,988
That sucks.

291
00:32:27,988 --> 00:32:30,108
Someone as smart as you should be competing.

292
00:32:32,148 --> 00:32:35,668
Don't feel bad. We still have our number one favorite.

293
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:39,828
This one... won't let us down.

294
00:32:42,748 --> 00:32:43,988
I'm gonna go.

295
00:32:44,108 --> 00:32:47,188
Hey, bye. Good luck.

296
00:32:47,588 --> 00:32:49,588
Bye, Earn.

297
00:32:50,028 --> 00:32:51,188
Hey, good luck.

298
00:32:51,188 --> 00:32:51,748
Thanks.

299
00:32:51,748 --> 00:32:52,828
Good luck to you both.

300
00:32:53,188 --> 00:32:54,108
Bye.

301
00:32:54,148 --> 00:32:56,068
Don't forget to win for us, Earn!

302
00:32:57,628 --> 00:32:58,668
Bye.

303
00:33:08,508 --> 00:33:10,108
Might as well just show up tomorrow.

304
00:33:13,068 --> 00:33:14,428
Well.

305
00:33:15,188 --> 00:33:17,068
So crazy over a guy that you got in trouble, huh?

306
00:33:17,748 --> 00:33:20,068
Don't let your behavior score drop too low.

307
00:33:20,828 --> 00:33:23,148
Or the school will ban you from cheerleading.

308
00:33:23,548 --> 00:33:25,388
And everyone else will suffer.

309
00:33:25,388 --> 00:33:27,188
I don't need a lecture from someone like you.

310
00:33:27,188 --> 00:33:28,588
What's wrong with someone like me?

311
00:33:28,828 --> 00:33:32,188
At least I never sold out my friends like you did.

312
00:33:32,188 --> 00:33:33,868
If you'd just paid me back, this wouldn't have happened.

313
00:33:33,868 --> 00:33:35,188
I did pay you back.

314
00:33:35,188 --> 00:33:37,748
You were the one who wanted to go bite Belle yourself.

315
00:33:38,668 --> 00:33:40,268
I suggest you keep your mouth shut

316
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:42,148
and use it to borrow money like always, Nano.

317
00:33:42,148 --> 00:33:44,188
Don't start with me.

318
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:46,788
Don't think I wouldn't dare.

319
00:33:46,788 --> 00:33:47,668
I dare.

320
00:33:47,668 --> 00:33:48,588
So what?

321
00:33:48,588 --> 00:33:49,548
I dare too.

322
00:33:49,548 --> 00:33:50,708
You said you dared.

323
00:33:50,708 --> 00:33:51,588
You start then.

324
00:33:51,588 --> 00:33:52,868
Bring it on if you dare.

325
00:33:52,908 --> 00:33:53,428
Why?

326
00:33:53,428 --> 00:33:54,628
And why?

327
00:33:54,628 --> 00:33:55,828
And you?

328
00:34:07,148 --> 00:34:08,668
I'm okay.

329
00:34:09,908 --> 00:34:11,308
Jane.

330
00:34:11,508 --> 00:34:12,668
Are you okay?

331
00:34:20,788 --> 00:34:21,988
Idiot.

332
00:34:22,348 --> 00:34:24,588
Did you really think I was gonna slap Khaopan?

333
00:34:25,828 --> 00:34:28,428
Well... you look like the type.

334
00:34:31,068 --> 00:34:33,428
Just kidding.

335
00:34:37,548 --> 00:34:40,468
But honestly, I almost did.

336
00:34:41,108 --> 00:34:44,268
Good thing you didn't. Good effort holding back.

337
00:34:44,268 --> 00:34:46,268
Sports day is almost here.

338
00:34:46,268 --> 00:34:49,668
Don't let a problem between two people ruin it for the whole team.

339
00:34:49,668 --> 00:34:51,468
Just compromise when you can.

340
00:34:52,308 --> 00:34:53,788
Think of the greater good.

341
00:34:58,148 --> 00:35:00,108
You sound just like my grandma.

342
00:35:04,588 --> 00:35:08,148
I'm gonna knock you on the head, Nano dear.

343
00:35:09,628 --> 00:35:11,068
I'm not doing this anymore.

344
00:35:11,068 --> 00:35:13,868
Ow, still hurts!

345
00:36:07,708 --> 00:36:11,068
It's alright. Amy, please make yourself comfortable.

346
00:36:55,268 --> 00:36:57,628
I've heard the song you wrote, Amy.

347
00:36:58,348 --> 00:37:00,068
It's a lovely song.

348
00:37:00,348 --> 00:37:01,948
Thank you, Ma'am.

349
00:37:03,068 --> 00:37:04,588
Did you write it for your boyfriend?

350
00:37:05,268 --> 00:37:07,188
I don't have a boyfriend yet.

351
00:37:07,948 --> 00:37:09,068
Oh?

352
00:37:09,588 --> 00:37:11,188
But that's nice.

353
00:37:11,428 --> 00:37:13,548
You seem like a romantic, Amy.

354
00:37:14,468 --> 00:37:17,068
It reminds me of when I was a young woman.

355
00:37:17,068 --> 00:37:19,388
You still look very young now, Ma'am.

356
00:37:20,548 --> 00:37:23,548
Actually, I'm not that conservative, you know.

357
00:37:24,308 --> 00:37:28,188
Love isn't a bad thing.

358
00:37:28,468 --> 00:37:31,948
My Sophie is almost a full-grown woman.

359
00:37:32,428 --> 00:37:35,228
If someone really came along and courted her...

360
00:37:35,228 --> 00:37:37,348
I wouldn't mind.

361
00:37:41,188 --> 00:37:43,348
And if someone does try to win Sophie's heart...

362
00:37:43,348 --> 00:37:46,948
I'd like you to help keep an eye on them, Amy.

363
00:37:46,948 --> 00:37:48,708
I trust you.

364
00:37:51,108 --> 00:37:52,308
Okay.

365
00:37:53,468 --> 00:37:57,228
I'm going to go talk to my friend who owns the resort.

366
00:37:57,228 --> 00:37:58,948
If you two want to take a walk,

367
00:37:58,948 --> 00:38:02,028
or take some photos, feel free.

368
00:38:30,108 --> 00:38:33,308
It seems like your mom would be okay with it now

369
00:38:33,308 --> 00:38:35,228
if you had a partner, So.

370
00:40:10,599 --> 00:40:12,599
At first, I thought we'd go to your place.

371
00:40:13,359 --> 00:40:15,799
Well, if we're going to study...

372
00:40:15,799 --> 00:40:18,119
and then I need you to help me take pictures after...

373
00:40:18,759 --> 00:40:20,079
This place seemed appropriate.

374
00:40:24,599 --> 00:40:26,399
How did you get into making this kind of content?

375
00:40:32,039 --> 00:40:35,479
Actually, someone I know invited me.

376
00:40:37,839 --> 00:40:39,159
Teacher Som.

377
00:40:42,719 --> 00:40:44,279
You know her, right?

378
00:40:50,079 --> 00:40:51,359
But you're okay, right?

379
00:40:52,519 --> 00:40:54,279
There aren't any problems, are there?

380
00:40:54,759 --> 00:40:58,599
Honestly, I don't really want to work with Teacher Som anymore.

381
00:40:59,039 --> 00:41:00,959
She wants me to show my face.

382
00:41:01,319 --> 00:41:02,919
Says the clients like it.

383
00:41:03,799 --> 00:41:05,399
But I refused.

384
00:41:08,799 --> 00:41:09,839
Well...

385
00:41:12,119 --> 00:41:14,159
You have to tell her straight up. That's right.

386
00:41:16,239 --> 00:41:17,919
It's completely your right to choose, Earn.

387
00:41:19,559 --> 00:41:20,839
Don't be afraid.

388
00:41:22,919 --> 00:41:24,079
Yeah.

389
00:41:25,159 --> 00:41:26,439
So...

390
00:41:28,159 --> 00:41:29,679
Let's get back to studying.

391
00:41:30,719 --> 00:41:33,319
Actually, I made a bit of a summary.

392
00:41:33,959 --> 00:41:35,519
So you wouldn't have to read too much.

393
00:41:35,519 --> 00:41:38,559
And just in case it might earn some extra points.

394
00:41:39,679 --> 00:41:40,959
So motivated.

395
00:41:49,479 --> 00:41:51,839
It requires a great deal of patience

396
00:41:51,839 --> 00:41:55,999
to build a genuine connection between two people.

397
00:42:00,359 --> 00:42:03,279
You must gradually approach each other.

398
00:42:03,279 --> 00:42:05,799
Sit far apart at first,

399
00:42:05,799 --> 00:42:09,079
then get closer day by day.

400
00:42:09,079 --> 00:42:11,599
Until trust is built,

401
00:42:11,599 --> 00:42:14,919
forming a special bond.

402
00:42:17,239 --> 00:42:19,919
When the rose began to bloom,

403
00:42:19,919 --> 00:42:24,119
the little prince felt excited and watched over her closely.

404
00:42:24,759 --> 00:42:27,319
He watered her every morning.

405
00:42:27,319 --> 00:42:30,799
Shielded her from the wind with a screen.

406
00:42:30,799 --> 00:42:35,439
And placed a glass globe over her

407
00:42:35,439 --> 00:42:38,279
to protect her from the cold at night.

408
00:42:40,439 --> 00:42:45,079
The rose often demanded attention

409
00:42:45,079 --> 00:42:48,959
by complaining and acting temperamental.

410
00:42:49,279 --> 00:42:54,039
Like complaining that the wind was too strong.

411
00:42:54,039 --> 00:42:56,599
Or the air was too cold.

412
00:43:01,199 --> 00:43:07,279
Therefore, the little prince quickly began to doubt her.

413
00:43:07,479 --> 00:43:11,839
Despite the good intentions from his love,

414
00:43:12,479 --> 00:43:18,159
he took insignificant words too seriously

415
00:43:18,159 --> 00:43:22,279
and became very unhappy.

416
00:43:32,119 --> 00:43:33,319
So.

417
00:43:36,919 --> 00:43:38,919
Can I ask you something?

418
00:43:40,159 --> 00:43:41,399
Yeah?

419
00:43:42,359 --> 00:43:45,279
Do you... like me?

420
00:43:48,079 --> 00:43:51,719
Like how normal people like each other?

421
00:43:55,999 --> 00:43:57,399
I think...

422
00:44:00,239 --> 00:44:02,279
I think about you all the time.

423
00:44:03,079 --> 00:44:04,159
And...

424
00:44:05,679 --> 00:44:07,679
I worry about you too.

425
00:44:09,799 --> 00:44:13,759
I'm afraid you don't feel the same way I do.

426
00:44:24,199 --> 00:44:26,639
I've never been like this with anyone before.

427
00:44:32,439 --> 00:44:34,199
If you're with me...

428
00:44:36,199 --> 00:44:39,679
I promise I won't get involved with anyone else.

429
00:44:41,239 --> 00:44:44,159
And I'll never do anything to hurt you.

430
00:44:50,239 --> 00:44:52,319
I love you, Sophie.

431
00:45:00,999 --> 00:45:02,359
You know?

432
00:45:04,079 --> 00:45:06,719
Before this, I never thought about love.

433
00:45:11,239 --> 00:45:12,919
I felt like...

434
00:45:14,319 --> 00:45:18,759
Just getting through each day was enough of a headache.

435
00:45:21,039 --> 00:45:23,279
Why add love to the mix?

436
00:45:26,359 --> 00:45:28,119
But once I got to know you...

437
00:45:29,039 --> 00:45:30,519
I realized,

438
00:45:31,719 --> 00:45:33,719
love really is a headache.

439
00:45:39,159 --> 00:45:41,439
But it's a headache worth having.

440
00:45:45,919 --> 00:45:47,559
Are you saying you love me?

441
00:45:48,519 --> 00:45:50,439
You're so slow to catch on.

442
00:45:51,839 --> 00:45:53,759
Then let's be girlfriends.

443
00:46:00,119 --> 00:46:03,439
You don't have to give me an answer right now.

444
00:46:04,239 --> 00:46:07,519
I know this is probably moving too fast for you.

445
00:46:09,519 --> 00:46:12,199
But if one day,

446
00:46:12,439 --> 00:46:14,039
I like you more than this,

447
00:46:15,759 --> 00:46:17,759
to the point where I want to make things official,

448
00:46:19,719 --> 00:46:21,719
I might ask you to be my girlfriend again.

449
00:46:22,799 --> 00:46:27,479
And if you're still not ready then...

450
00:46:27,479 --> 00:46:29,079
I think...

451
00:46:29,759 --> 00:46:31,919
I might really have to give up.

452
00:46:46,519 --> 00:46:48,599
Thank you for understanding.

453
00:48:51,559 --> 00:48:52,519
Hello.

454
00:48:52,519 --> 00:48:56,759
Hello, Ma'am. I'm calling from Anna Patronage Tipwan School.

455
00:48:57,839 --> 00:49:01,319
From the school? What is it, teacher?

456
00:49:01,839 --> 00:49:06,359
I've received a report about Sophie's inappropriate behavior.

457
00:49:06,359 --> 00:49:09,639
Regarding her dating a female friend.

458
00:49:10,599 --> 00:49:12,479
Are you sure, teacher?

459
00:49:12,919 --> 00:49:14,599
That Sophie...

460
00:49:15,239 --> 00:49:17,799
is dating a girl?

461
00:49:18,999 --> 00:49:22,199
Were you already aware of this, Ma'am?

462
00:49:24,839 --> 00:49:26,279
Thank you.

463
00:49:48,559 --> 00:49:50,839
Hmm, this outfit is nice.

464
00:49:51,279 --> 00:49:52,959
Not as revealing as the other day.

465
00:49:59,439 --> 00:50:01,039
Does the pose have to be like this?

466
00:50:01,359 --> 00:50:04,199
Well... the subscribers want this kind of thing.

467
00:50:04,199 --> 00:50:05,799
An angle of you on top?

468
00:50:05,799 --> 00:50:07,839
Hmm, don't talk.

469
00:50:09,159 --> 00:50:10,239
Okay.

470
00:50:23,959 --> 00:50:27,279
I think I need to lean in a little closer.

471
00:50:58,959 --> 00:51:00,439
Sorry.

472
00:51:35,719 --> 00:51:37,479
I think it looks sexier.

473
00:51:45,239 --> 00:51:46,599
Let's look at the pictures.

474
00:51:52,359 --> 00:51:53,479
Looks good.

475
00:52:16,279 --> 00:52:17,679
Thank you.

476
00:52:34,359 --> 00:52:36,519
How was swimming? Did you have fun?

477
00:52:36,839 --> 00:52:38,519
Very relaxing, Ma'am.

478
00:52:43,759 --> 00:52:46,559
Cherries are one of my favorite fruits.

479
00:52:46,799 --> 00:52:48,879
They're sweet and a bit sour.

480
00:52:49,279 --> 00:52:50,799
I could eat them forever.

481
00:52:51,759 --> 00:52:54,079
But if you buy them from a regular market,

482
00:52:54,079 --> 00:52:56,879
they might taste bland.

483
00:52:57,479 --> 00:52:59,439
It's disappointing.

484
00:52:59,799 --> 00:53:01,919
I'm lucky I have a regular shop.

485
00:53:02,879 --> 00:53:06,719
No matter how many times I order, it tastes the same.

486
00:53:07,079 --> 00:53:08,359
Never changes.

487
00:53:12,479 --> 00:53:14,199
But there was this one time,

488
00:53:15,799 --> 00:53:20,119
I asked Sophie's father to buy some cherries for me.

489
00:53:20,479 --> 00:53:23,679
I specifically told him to buy them from the usual shop.

490
00:53:25,039 --> 00:53:27,439
Even though that shop had been closed for a long time.

491
00:53:32,519 --> 00:53:33,919
But her father...

492
00:53:34,919 --> 00:53:37,079
brought them to me and said

493
00:53:37,079 --> 00:53:39,519
he bought them from the same shop.

494
00:53:55,559 --> 00:53:57,559
I hate liars.

495
00:54:01,519 --> 00:54:04,439
Liars who think I'm stupid.

496
00:54:06,279 --> 00:54:09,639
Sophie, you know I don't like liars, right?

497
00:54:12,879 --> 00:54:14,559
People who think I'm stupid.

498
00:54:15,079 --> 00:54:18,119
You know I hate them, right?

499
00:54:26,279 --> 00:54:28,239
I don't have to talk about your father.

500
00:54:30,599 --> 00:54:34,399
Because today is your birthday, Sophie.

501
00:54:37,439 --> 00:54:40,079
And it's time for an important moment.

502
00:54:58,159 --> 00:54:59,959
Happy Birthday, sweetie.

503
00:55:04,039 --> 00:55:10,159
Happy Birthday to you.

504
00:55:10,359 --> 00:55:14,879
Happy Birthday to you.

505
00:55:14,999 --> 00:55:20,399
Happy birthday... Happy birthday.

506
00:55:20,399 --> 00:55:24,959
Happy birthday to you.

507
00:55:28,319 --> 00:55:30,119
Happy birthday, honey.

508
00:55:30,679 --> 00:55:32,799
I wish for my daughter...

509
00:55:33,599 --> 00:55:36,879
to be a good girl for me forever.

510
00:55:37,559 --> 00:55:39,759
As my daughter grows up,

511
00:55:39,759 --> 00:55:42,639
I wish you a good, happy life.

512
00:55:43,719 --> 00:55:45,839
A good life partner.

513
00:55:46,399 --> 00:55:48,439
A warm family.

514
00:55:51,399 --> 00:55:53,759
I might be a bit old-fashioned.

515
00:55:54,799 --> 00:55:57,999
I know people these days might accept and support

516
00:55:57,999 --> 00:56:00,959
their children being whatever they want.

517
00:56:02,159 --> 00:56:06,279
But for me... my daughter,

518
00:56:09,199 --> 00:56:12,759
dating someone of the same sex... I don't think I could handle that.

519
00:56:13,759 --> 00:56:15,759
I'd rather die.

520
00:56:18,599 --> 00:56:21,279
Blow out the candles and receive my blessing, dear.

521
00:56:39,919 --> 00:56:41,759
Happy Birthday, sweetie.

522
00:57:48,250 --> 00:57:50,130
She'd really rather die?

523
00:57:57,890 --> 00:57:59,570
That's just how my mom is.

524
00:58:00,650 --> 00:58:03,210
Hey, don't cry.

525
00:58:09,930 --> 00:58:13,170
So... what do we do now?

526
00:58:16,570 --> 00:58:18,010
Well...

527
00:58:19,050 --> 00:58:20,450
Nothing.

528
00:58:21,690 --> 00:58:23,570
Just be friends like before.

529
00:58:31,450 --> 00:58:33,490
It's fine, Amy.

530
00:58:35,050 --> 00:58:37,250
It's been okay so far, right?

531
00:58:39,770 --> 00:58:41,810
We just won't be open about it.

532
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:47,610
I don't have a problem with that, So.

533
00:58:48,490 --> 00:58:50,370
But I will have a problem

534
00:58:50,370 --> 00:58:52,810
if we have to hide this from your mom for the rest of our lives.

535
00:58:55,410 --> 00:58:57,090
Right, So?

536
00:59:11,690 --> 00:59:13,690
I'm sorry, Amy.

537
00:59:20,370 --> 00:59:27,490
The rose tried to hide her feelings.

538
00:59:28,970 --> 00:59:33,450
Even though she felt sad, the rose refused to show her pain.

539
00:59:35,090 --> 00:59:37,010
The rose said she had been foolish,

540
00:59:37,010 --> 00:59:39,530
and apologized to the little prince,

541
00:59:39,530 --> 00:59:42,650
wishing him happiness.

542
01:00:16,450 --> 01:00:17,730
Ma'am.

543
01:00:23,490 --> 01:00:25,250
It's late. You're not asleep yet?

544
01:00:27,210 --> 01:00:30,290
The song I wrote... I wrote it for Sophie.

545
01:00:31,570 --> 01:00:33,610
I love Sophie.

546
01:00:33,610 --> 01:00:37,010
And no matter what happens, I won't give up.

547
01:00:40,290 --> 01:00:42,330
Sophie loves me too.

548
01:00:48,330 --> 01:00:50,170
Did Sophie tell you that?

549
01:00:52,170 --> 01:00:54,410
Please give Sophie and me another chance.

550
01:01:30,170 --> 01:01:31,450
Ma'am!

551
01:01:31,890 --> 01:01:33,730
What's wrong?

552
01:01:33,850 --> 01:01:35,890
Ma'am... Ma'am, calm down.

553
01:01:35,890 --> 01:01:38,050
Go back! Go back!

554
01:01:38,050 --> 01:01:38,730
Calm down, Ma'am.

555
01:01:38,730 --> 01:01:39,890
I said go back!

556
01:01:40,290 --> 01:01:41,490
I said go back!

557
01:01:41,490 --> 01:01:45,610
Go back! Go back!

558
01:01:45,610 --> 01:01:47,610
Go back! Go back! Do you hear me?!

559
01:01:47,610 --> 01:01:51,010
Go back! Go back!

560
01:01:51,530 --> 01:01:53,810
So! I don't know what's wrong with your mom.

561
01:01:53,810 --> 01:01:55,330
Mom, stop.

562
01:01:55,530 --> 01:01:57,330
Just go.

563
01:01:58,770 --> 01:02:00,130
Mom.

564
01:02:00,490 --> 01:02:02,530
Please go back now.

565
01:02:02,810 --> 01:02:05,330
So, I'm trying to help you!

566
01:02:14,730 --> 01:02:16,810
I'm here now, Mom.

567
01:02:40,290 --> 01:02:41,970
So, Som, what are you doing these days?

568
01:02:41,970 --> 01:02:46,090
I'm a teacher now. Tutoring. I have a lot of students lately.

569
01:02:46,090 --> 01:02:47,170
You're so hardworking.

570
01:02:47,170 --> 01:02:49,650
I actually have to look for more teachers right now.

571
01:02:49,650 --> 01:02:51,050
Oh, Earn.

572
01:02:51,050 --> 01:02:54,050
You're back just in time. Som is here to see you.

573
01:02:54,050 --> 01:02:56,770
She came to ask if you're still tutoring.

574
01:02:56,770 --> 01:02:58,370
She wants to give you some students.

575
01:02:59,210 --> 01:03:01,650
I told her you're still doing it.

576
01:03:01,650 --> 01:03:04,610
But you already tutor a lot.

577
01:03:10,850 --> 01:03:12,530
Why did you do this?

578
01:03:12,530 --> 01:03:15,010
We promised not to tell my mom about this.

579
01:03:15,890 --> 01:03:18,010
I wasn't going to tell her.

580
01:03:18,370 --> 01:03:20,450
I was just making conversation.

581
01:03:23,330 --> 01:03:24,850
Then why are you here?

582
01:03:26,210 --> 01:03:28,810
You weren't answering my texts.

583
01:03:28,810 --> 01:03:30,370
So I had to come see you.

584
01:03:30,370 --> 01:03:32,890
You just keep asking me to show my face.

585
01:03:32,890 --> 01:03:34,330
I'm not doing it.

586
01:03:34,690 --> 01:03:36,730
Earn, I'll be honest with you.

587
01:03:38,490 --> 01:03:40,370
I'm really strapped for cash right now.

588
01:03:41,490 --> 01:03:44,010
And what the clients requested isn't that hard, is it?

589
01:03:44,010 --> 01:03:45,690
It pays 150,000, Earn.

590
01:03:45,690 --> 01:03:47,410
Then go find someone else to do it.

591
01:03:47,410 --> 01:03:49,090
When you were in trouble,

592
01:03:49,290 --> 01:03:51,210
I was there to help you, wasn't I?

593
01:03:51,730 --> 01:03:55,610
And now that I'm in trouble, you won't help me?

594
01:03:57,410 --> 01:03:59,010
Show some sympathy, will you?

595
01:04:00,090 --> 01:04:02,370
I don't want to do this forever, you know.

596
01:04:10,570 --> 01:04:12,770
Hit it, hit it, hit it!

597
01:04:16,490 --> 01:04:17,690
Where are you going? You can't go.

598
01:04:18,170 --> 01:04:22,250
[The cheerleading outfits are ready. Please transfer the remaining 50% to this account.]

599
01:04:23,730 --> 01:04:25,650
So cute.

600
01:04:31,570 --> 01:04:32,810
Sis.

601
01:04:33,690 --> 01:04:35,290
Are you gonna borrow money again?

602
01:04:36,530 --> 01:04:40,290
Pretty, smart sister, can I borrow ten thousand?

603
01:04:40,370 --> 01:04:42,890
Huh? Ten thousand?

604
01:04:44,410 --> 01:04:48,090
I don't think this is funny anymore. You haven't even paid me back for last time.

605
01:04:48,090 --> 01:04:52,090
And recently I saw you had some work done on your face. Where did you get the money for that?

606
01:04:57,770 --> 01:04:59,370
Do you have a sugar daddy?

607
01:04:59,370 --> 01:05:03,130
Ugh, nonsense. What sugar daddy?

608
01:05:03,130 --> 01:05:05,770
If I had one, why would I be borrowing money from you?

609
01:05:08,650 --> 01:05:09,890
Who knows?

610
01:05:11,770 --> 01:05:13,130
Yeah, yeah.

611
01:05:13,290 --> 01:05:15,250
I borrowed money from friends.

612
01:05:15,650 --> 01:05:17,610
Several of them, to tide me over.

613
01:05:17,610 --> 01:05:19,530
I'm gradually paying them back.

614
01:05:21,370 --> 01:05:23,370
Nano, if your friends...

615
01:05:23,370 --> 01:05:25,890
suddenly wanted all their money back at once...

616
01:05:26,370 --> 01:05:27,850
Wouldn't you be screwed?

617
01:05:28,330 --> 01:05:29,970
Probably not.

618
01:05:31,290 --> 01:05:33,490
I'm paying them back.

619
01:05:33,490 --> 01:05:35,370
What are you spending all this money on?

620
01:05:35,370 --> 01:05:38,770
I see you shopping like crazy on IG, then getting work done on your face.

621
01:05:38,770 --> 01:05:41,850
Ugh, Sis, you ask too many questions. Never mind.

622
01:05:41,850 --> 01:05:44,650
Hey, you brat.

623
01:05:51,189 --> 01:05:53,183
[- Can I have my money back now?]
[- Mine's a small amount. Pay me first.]

624
01:05:53,498 --> 01:05:56,974
[- Are you okay, Nano?]
[- Isn't this a bit much?]

625
01:06:01,690 --> 01:06:04,050
Why is everyone asking for it back at the same time?

626
01:06:10,326 --> 01:06:12,548
I have some secret to tell you.

627
01:06:14,350 --> 01:06:17,076
Actually, I have a birthmark on my forehead.

628
01:06:19,644 --> 01:06:21,934
Don't I get any of your smile?

629
01:06:46,970 --> 01:06:49,490
Hey. How are you doing?

630
01:06:50,890 --> 01:06:52,370
How am I doing about what?

631
01:06:52,730 --> 01:06:54,410
About your mom.

632
01:06:56,890 --> 01:06:57,970
Well...

633
01:06:59,450 --> 01:07:00,890
Nothing much.

634
01:07:01,570 --> 01:07:03,090
She's my mom.

635
01:07:03,890 --> 01:07:05,810
I've lived with her since I was born.

636
01:07:08,290 --> 01:07:09,650
Anyway...

637
01:07:11,050 --> 01:07:12,650
I'm sorry.

638
01:07:13,010 --> 01:07:14,610
For scaring you.

639
01:07:21,690 --> 01:07:24,250
You don't have to carry everything by yourself, you know.

640
01:07:25,530 --> 01:07:27,130
What you're going through...

641
01:07:28,170 --> 01:07:30,810
It's too heavy for one person to bear alone.

642
01:07:35,610 --> 01:07:38,210
But I've carried it alone my whole life.

643
01:07:39,250 --> 01:07:41,050
And I've always gotten through it.

644
01:07:44,010 --> 01:07:45,450
You know what, Sophie?

645
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:48,170
From the day I met your mom...

646
01:07:48,770 --> 01:07:50,250
until right now...

647
01:07:51,610 --> 01:07:55,850
There hasn't been a single moment where I felt like walking away from you.

648
01:07:59,370 --> 01:08:00,610
So...

649
01:08:01,330 --> 01:08:03,050
Please don't push me away.

650
01:08:04,810 --> 01:08:08,330
Let me be by your side when you're not okay.

651
01:08:20,170 --> 01:08:22,090
Be my girlfriend, Sophie.

652
01:08:33,730 --> 01:08:36,570
Don't make this any worse than it already is, Amy.

653
01:08:40,250 --> 01:08:44,130
With anything else, I could probably think of a way out.

654
01:08:46,490 --> 01:08:49,490
But I really can't see my mom as the problem.

655
01:08:51,450 --> 01:08:54,250
I don't want to live my life feeling like...

656
01:08:55,210 --> 01:08:56,810
I hate my mom.

657
01:08:58,250 --> 01:08:59,730
I feel like...

658
01:09:00,290 --> 01:09:02,530
The only way out for me...

659
01:09:03,010 --> 01:09:06,450
Is to be reborn. Or for one of us to die.

660
01:09:07,770 --> 01:09:10,650
No one can help me with this anyway, Amy.

661
01:09:11,530 --> 01:09:15,290
I can, So. I can help you.

662
01:09:15,290 --> 01:09:19,130
If you don't want the issue with your mom to be a problem for you,

663
01:09:19,410 --> 01:09:22,090
then it won't be a problem for me either.

664
01:09:22,770 --> 01:09:23,930
Or if...

665
01:09:25,570 --> 01:09:28,490
You want to keep our relationship a secret forever,

666
01:09:29,290 --> 01:09:30,850
I'm okay with that.

667
01:09:32,290 --> 01:09:34,810
Just as long as I can still be by your side.

668
01:09:37,810 --> 01:09:39,730
Thank you, Amy.

669
01:09:41,330 --> 01:09:44,010
I've been really happy with you.

670
01:09:45,850 --> 01:09:48,890
But I want you to go back to living your life.

671
01:09:49,770 --> 01:09:52,770
Without having to worry about me anymore.

672
01:10:03,370 --> 01:10:04,890
Okay...

673
01:10:10,690 --> 01:10:13,490
Please. Don't go.

674
01:10:29,210 --> 01:10:31,130
I'm done lying to myself.

675
01:10:33,810 --> 01:10:36,050
And you shouldn't lie to yourself anymore either.

676
01:11:28,970 --> 01:11:32,650
Finally, the moment everyone has been waiting for!

677
01:11:32,650 --> 01:11:35,730
The show from the cheerleaders of all four colors!

678
01:11:40,970 --> 01:11:44,330
Let me tell you, this year is going to be fierce.

679
01:11:44,330 --> 01:11:46,330
Every color is giving it their all.

680
01:11:46,330 --> 01:11:49,890
Alright, let's start with the first color. The Blue Team!

681
01:12:27,370 --> 01:12:29,330
We are absolutely not losing today.

682
01:12:29,330 --> 01:12:32,970
If we do it like we practiced, we'll definitely win.

683
01:12:32,970 --> 01:12:36,010
Ready? One, two, three.

684
01:12:36,010 --> 01:12:37,370
Hey!

685
01:12:39,970 --> 01:12:42,450
Good luck, both of you!

686
01:12:54,210 --> 01:12:55,890
Nano, have you seen this?

687
01:12:55,890 --> 01:12:57,210
What is it?

688
01:13:02,050 --> 01:13:04,570
[#FakeRichGreenCheerleader #APT]
[Total of 293,000. Better ask for your money back before it's gone.]

689
01:13:04,570 --> 01:13:06,610
[Getting rich from other people's money. lol]

690
01:13:15,570 --> 01:13:17,330
No need to thank me.

691
01:13:18,770 --> 01:13:20,810
For taking the trouble to sum up your debts.

692
01:13:28,770 --> 01:13:30,410
It was you.

